/-
# MiniFundamentalGroup.Advanced.HigherHomotopy

Higher homotopy groups π_n(X, x₀) for n ≥ 2:
- Definition: π_n = [(S^n, *), (X, x₀)] (homotopy classes of maps)
- π_n is abelian for n ≥ 2
- π_n is a functor from Top* to Ab (abelian groups)
- Relationship to homology: Hurewicz theorem
- Whitehead theorem: weak homotopy equivalence
- Long exact sequence of a fibration
- Eilenberg-MacLane spaces K(G, n)
-/
import MiniFundamentalGroup.Core.Basic
import MiniFundamentalGroup.Core.GroupStructure
import MiniFundamentalGroup.Core.Functoriality

